misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the trip cost is computed by first finding gallons used (distance ÷ mpg) and then multiplying by price per gallon.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: this matches the correct execution model and formula for fuel cost. Java will evaluate the doubles as expected (floating-point division/multiplication).
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None for valid inputs (mpg > 0, price >= 0). Output matches the required computation; formatting may differ only in number of decimals, which is typically acceptable unless rounding was explicitly required.
